&lt;h1 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CSS forms the basis of styling of web pages. With CSS, you can apply styles to make your web pages more readable and beautiful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All CSS in a webpage go inside a &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;style&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/style&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag, unless you are linking CSS from other files. All CSS are composed of CSS rulesets, which are the basic building block of CSS code. They look like this.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;figure class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;
  &lt;figcaption&gt;
  	&lt;span&gt;A typical CSS Selector&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;codewrapper&#34;&gt;
    &lt;table class=&#34;highlighttable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;linenodiv&#34; style=&#34;background-color: #f0f0f0; padding-right: 10px&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;line-height: 125%&#34;&gt;1
2
3&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34; style=&#34;background: #272822&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;line-height: 125%&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f92672&#34;&gt;div&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f92672&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;blue;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The first part &lt;code&gt;div&lt;/code&gt; is called a selector, and the next part is called a declaration.&lt;/p&gt;

